{
  "texts": [
    "Velocity has only the perturbation component, v = v 1, as it is assumed to be zero in the state of equilibrium.",
    "The equilibrium state strictly assumes magnetohydrostatic (MHS) equilibrium in the absence of external forces (v = 0 and S = 0) to be fulfilled,",
    "The set of equilibrium variables used in the initialization phase of a simulation must be consistent with this definition.",
    "Many different kinds of equilibrium fulfill Eq. 45.",
    "For example, a force-free equilibrium or a potential magnetic field equilibrium, where the gravitationally stratified thermodynamic variables are independent of the magnetic variables, can be used to initiate a simulation with MANCHA3D."
  ]
}